{"id":"foreknowledge-of-god","term":"Foreknowledge of God","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p><a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Acts 2:23\">Acts 2:23</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Romans 8:29\">Rom. 8:29</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Romans 11:2\">11:2</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Peter 1:2\">1 Pet. 1:2</a>), one of those high attributes essentially appertaining to him the full import of which we cannot comprehend. In the most absolute sense his knowledge is infinite (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Samuel 23:9\">1 Sam. 23:9-13</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Jeremiah 38:17\">Jer. 38:17-23</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Jeremiah 42:9\">42:9-22</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Matthew 11:21\">Matt. 11:21</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Matthew 11:23\">23</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Acts 15:18\">Acts 15:18</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Acts 2:23","Romans 8:29","Romans 11:2","1 Peter 1:2","1 Samuel 23:9","Jeremiah 38:17","Jeremiah 42:9","Matthew 11:21","Matthew 11:23","Acts 15:18"]}